commit.message: Bump VERSION to 0.12.7
Updates to read_config() for PROCESSORS parameter.
Update Docs for PROCESSORS lrzip.conf paramater.
Create shortcut for lrzip-next, lrzn. Remove .PHONY directive in Makefile.am. Update manpage.
Bump Version to 0.12.6

Fix #151. fake_mremap, used on non-linux systems, does not compile (Nick Chan). Revert f7a5891.

@asdfugil reports that the fatal() macro call is missing the control
structure and this causes compile to fail. This fix replaces the
fatal() call with a fprintf(stderr, ...) and exit.

Also removed duplicate #define in lrzip_private.h

Fix (again) #88. MacOS implementation of write() crashes when nmemb > 0x7fff0000. (Nick Chan).

Normally, write() will write at most 2G at a time, and continue
until the entire buffer is written. However, as @asdfugil pointed
out, if nmemb > 0x7fff0000, write() on MacOS will return an
error 22 - Invalid Argument. This commit limits nmemb to 0x7fff0000.
Bump VERSION to 0.12.5
Handle zstd compression errors properly. Return codes are negative. ENUM values are positive. #148

Expand buffer length in lz4_compresses from 10MB to 100MB.

Since ram speed is not a factor, there is no harm in expanding
the test buffer size. This will also aid zpaq compression
directly which uses compression estimate from lz4 to compute
the redundancy field in the method. LB,RED,TYPE.
Prevent show_version() from printing twice.
Bump VERSION to 0.12.4
BUGFIX: #144 . double free detected in tcache 2

Update Makefile.am to add LICENSES to doc dir.

Add SPDX License Identifiers. Add LICENSES Directory for all code.
Add SPDX License Identifiers. Add LICENSES Directory for all code.
Update and clean TODO list.
Add obsolete message.
Set rzip compression level with zstd.
Bump VERSION to 0.12.3
Use lzo1x_999_compress() for compression level 9.
Sync lrzip-fe to v0.80
Minor update to speedtest.sh
Updates to speedtest.sh
Use getopt() for speedtest.sh. Add new options for specifying testfile and extra compression options.

Major updates to speedtest.sh program

Will output to a CSV file with all timing and stats
data for compression and decompression for selected
methods and levels. See usage message for info.

Updates to lrzip.conf processing.

* remove print_output macros.
* don't fatal abort if invalid parameter. Just reset to default.
* if VERBOSE set, print messages and parameter values.
* update documentation.
Make LZ4 disable warning print_verbose, not print_output.
Updates to speedtest to allow specific methods.
FIX #138. Don't fail on decompress/test/info with lesser compression methods.
Remove extra newlines in progress output.
